Madge Kennedy https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madge_Kennedy 0 Madge Kennedy (April 19, 1891 – June 9, 1987) was a stage, film and TV actress whose career began in the silent era. In 1921, journalist Heywood Broun described her as "the best farce actress in New York".
